Not only are these two abbreviations mistaken for one another, but that for aad is some· times taken for ai.⁸ Quod, qaia, quasi, qaoe, are all abbreviated by adding the proper sign to the simple q. As a result of this similarity they—especially the first two—are not always distinguished from one another by the scribes.⁴ More or less connected with these are another troublesome set of abbreviations built on the letter q. lV. Abbreviations which from their very form are ambiguous. These mean little or nothing definitely, and by themselves, and though their meaning is usually clear to us because of the context, they gave abundant opportunities for making mistakes to the copyist who was not troubling himself about the context. Many of them represent the quintessence of abbreviation.
